-- Iniesta, Messi and Xavi are Finalists for FIFA's Soccer Player of the Year
-- B y   C h r i s   E l s e r
-- 2010-12-06T12:05:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-06/iniesta-messi-and-xavi-are-finalists-for-fifa-s-soccer-player-of-the-year.html
Barcelona’s Andres Iniesta, Lionel
Messi and Xavi are the finalists for world player of the year,
soccer’s governing body said today.  The trio were the nominees for FIFA’s Ballon d’Or, which
will be awarded on Jan. 10. Iniesta and Xavi helped Spain win
this year’s World Cup, while Argentina’s Messi won the prize
last year.  Spain’s Vicente del Bosque and Barcelona’s Pep Guardiola
join Real Madrid’s Jose Mourinho as the nominees for men’s coach
of the year.  Germany’s Fatmire Bajramaj and Birgit Prinz along with
Brazil’s Marta are the women’s nominees for women player of the
year.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chris Elser at 
 celser@bloomberg.net  